text: I disagree with analyst on @cnbc who points out to dour investor sentiment as a sign of imminent market improvement. Sentiment is rarely a good timing tool.

@realmoneyOct 23, 2019 | 09:36 AM EDT DOUG KASS Will Social Media Be Disrupted? * The reduction in my social media stock exposure reflects the likely continued acceleration in legal, legislative and regulatory influences as we approach the November 2020 election

* As the rhetoric increases (with both the Democrats and Republicans having the industry in their bulls eye) the social media platforms will find themselves under more scrutiny and will likely face much higher costs * While the intermediate term outlook for $FB, $AMZN and $GOOGL

remains outstanding, the short term is being disrupted - putting a limit to social media's share price upside * I am comfortable with my current sizing and plan to continue to hold onto TWTR, AMZN and GOOGL even though the investment road ahead may be filled with political
